+
+## Claude tmux readiness and wrapper packaging validation
+
+Hive's gem file list now includes every shell script under
+`lib/hive/scripts/`, and the default integration suite builds a real temporary
+gem to verify that every literal launcher-path script reference exists in both
+source and the artifact. Claude tmux readiness now scans the last 12 nonblank
+lines of the current prompt region, accepts Unicode separator spaces adjacent
+to the idle caret, and requires all later lines to be recognized input-box
+separator or bypass-permissions footer chrome. Trust, permission, numbered-menu,
+embedded-output, and stale-caret panes remain non-ready.
+
+Added an isolated built-gem validation recipe to [[operating]]. It pins the
+invoked `hive` binary to the temporary install, checks the Compound Engineering
+plugin and `hive doctor`, and replays an execute-stage tmux task without manual
+script copying. The guide also separates this validation from stale
+systemd/launchd unit paths; daemon binary-drift repair remains out of scope.
