+### Validate a locally built gem with Claude tmux
+
+Before a patch release, validate the artifact rather than a source-checkout
+`bin/hive`. Build the gem into a temporary prefix, inspect its real payload,
+and install it without copying runtime scripts by hand:
+
+```bash
+repo_root=$PWD
+prefix=$(mktemp -d)
+gem_file="$prefix/hive-cli.gem"
+
+gem build "$repo_root/hive.gemspec" --output "$gem_file"
+ruby -rrubygems/package -e '
+  required = %w[
+    lib/hive/scripts/interactive_claude_wrapper.sh
+    lib/hive/scripts/stop_hook.sh
+  ]
+  missing = required - Gem::Package.new(ARGV.fetch(0)).contents
+  abort "missing packaged scripts: #{missing.join(", ")}" unless missing.empty?
+' "$gem_file"
+
+export GEM_HOME="$prefix/gems"
+export GEM_PATH="$GEM_HOME"
+export XDG_CONFIG_HOME="$prefix/xdg/config"
+export XDG_DATA_HOME="$prefix/xdg/data"
+export XDG_STATE_HOME="$prefix/xdg/state"
+export XDG_CACHE_HOME="$prefix/xdg/cache"
+export PATH="$GEM_HOME/bin:$PATH"
+
+gem install "$gem_file" --no-document
+hash -r
+hive_bin=$(command -v hive)
+test "$hive_bin" = "$GEM_HOME/bin/hive"
+"$hive_bin" --version
+```
+
+Keep the operator's normal `HOME` so Claude can see its installed Compound
+Engineering plugin, while the gem and all Hive XDG state stay under the
+temporary prefix. Confirm the plugin is listed, then run doctor from the
+project used for the replay; every required skill and tmux check should be
+green (a missing QMD row remains the documented warning-only exception):
+
+```bash
+claude plugin list | rg -i 'compound-engineering'
+cd /path/to/reproduced-project
+"$hive_bin" doctor
+```
+
+Replay an incident-shaped task by addressing its existing execute-stage folder
+directly. The task should use `claude.mode: tmux` and include enough work to
+exercise prompt submission after Claude paints its input-box separators and
+footer:
+
+```bash
+task_dir="$PWD/.hive-state/stages/4-execute/<incident-task-slug>"
+"$hive_bin" run "$task_dir" --json
+"$hive_bin" status --json
+```
+
+Success means the run reaches `WAITING`, `EXECUTE_COMPLETE`, or a later valid
+workflow marker without a readiness timeout and without manually copying either
+shell script into `GEM_HOME`. Preserve the prefix and task logs when the replay
+fails; remove `$prefix` after the validation evidence has been recorded.
+
+This direct invocation also avoids confusing the artifact under test with a
+stale daemon executable. A systemd user unit or launchd plist stores a resolved
+binary path and can continue running an older Hive until its unit is refreshed
+and restarted. Check `systemctl --user cat hive-daemon` or
+`~/Library/LaunchAgents/local.hive-daemon.plist` before interpreting a
+daemon-driven replay. Refreshing that installed unit is validation hygiene;
+automatic daemon binary-drift repair is outside this packaging/readiness fix.
+
 ## Prerequisites
 
 Once per workstation:
